// task_b.su — the Linux 0.00 "task B" analogue.
//
// Companion to task_a.su. Linux 0.00's task B writes 'B' forever;
// the timer interrupt alternates it with task A. Here it emits the
// ASCII codepoint of 'B' — 66 — as a real substrate number-vector
// via `real_number` (a substrate op, no host shortcut). The value
// genuinely is chr(66)=='B', decoded host-side by the monitoring
// `.real()` accessor — not a faked 'B'. The inbound axon (the
// tick / timer-IRQ analogue) is ignored, as in Linux 0.00.
//
// See planning/21-linux-0.00.md for the faithful-mapping rationale
// and the honest-scope limits (no bare-metal boot, no TSS — by
// Yantra architecture, on purpose).

function vector on_axon(vector input_axon) {
    return real_number(66.0);
}
